    statement: { description: "## Repeated DNA Subsequences\n\nA DNA sequence is composed of characters 'A', 'C', 'G', 'T'. Given a string `s` representing a DNA sequence, return all 10-letter-long subsequences (substrings) that occur more than once.", inputFormat: "A single line containing the DNA string `s`.", outputFormat: "Print each repeated 10-letter substring on a separate line, in the order of first appearance.", constraints: "1 ≤ |s| ≤ 10^5\n`s[i]` is 'A', 'C', 'G', or 'T'.", notes: "" },
