    hints: ["If |s1| + |s2| ≠ |s3|, return false immediately.","Use DP: dp[i][j] = can s3[0..i+j-1] be formed by s1[0..i-1] and s2[0..j-1].","dp[i][j] = (dp[i-1][j] && s1[i-1]==s3[i+j-1]) || (dp[i][j-1] && s2[j-1]==s3[i+j-1])."],
    editorial: { intuition: "DP table where dp[i][j] means the first i+j characters of s3 can be formed by the first i chars of s1 and first j chars of s2.", bruteForce: "Try all possible interleavings recursively. Time: O(2^(m+n)).", betterApproach: "Add memoization. Same time as optimal but recursive.", optimalApproach: "Bottom-up DP: dp[i][j] = true if s3[0..i+j-1] is valid interleaving. Check matching from s1 or s2. Time: O(m×n), Space: O(m×n) or O(n) optimized.", dryRun: "s1='aab', s2='axy', s3='aaxaby': dp table fills correctly → true", timeComplexity: "O(m × n)", spaceComplexity: "O(n) with space optimization", alternativeSolution: "BFS/DFS on state (i,j) with visited set.", interviewTips: "This is a classic 2D DP problem. Draw the DP table during the interview.", commonMistakes: "Length check: |s1|+|s2| must equal |s3|. Wrong DP transitions." },
